design.info:
Modernize your UI with these switch buttons instead of old checkboxes

```
<label class='switch'>
  <input type='checkbox'>
  <span class='slider'></span>
</label>
```

```
.switch input {display: none}
.switch, .slider {border-radius: 50px}
.switch {
  width: 70px;
  padding: 5px;
  box-sizing: border-box;
  display: inline-block;
}
.slider {
  width: 30px;
  height: 30px;
  transition: transform .2s ease-in-out;
}
.switch input:checked + .slider {
  transform: translateX(100%);
}
```

layout.info:
To center an inline element horizontally, such as an image or paragraph
```
.center-text {
  text-align: center;
}
```

To center a block element horizontally, simply set the margin to auto
```
.center-block {
  margin: auto;
}
```

To align an element in the perfect center (horizontally and vertically), a negative translate combined with absolute position can do the trick
```
.wrapper {
  position: relative;
}

.perfect-center {
  position: absolute;
  top: 50%;
  left: 50%;
  transform: translate(-50%, -50%);
}
```

flexbox.info:
A half half layout is 2 column layout each taking full height
```
<section class='wrapper'>
  <div class='child'>...</div>
  <div class='child>...</div>
</section>
```
```
.wrapper {
  display: flex;
}

.child {
  flex-grow: 1;
  flex-shrink: 1;
  flex-basis: 100%;
}
```
